HEADWORD: Sawhorse
<hw>Saw"horse`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of rack,
shaped like a double St. Andrew's cross, on which sticks of wood are
laid for sawing by hand; -- called also <altname>buck</altname>, and
<altname>sawbuck</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

